go-identify (2.2.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * INSTALLED MODULES: accept the current modules.json layout produced by newer
    go-modules versions (top-level object with schema_version / controller /
    slots fields). The previous reader only accepted a top-level list, so
    identify reported "No module configuration found" on controllers running a
    newer go-modules even though a valid modules.json was present. Both
    layouts are now supported; the legacy colon-separated file still takes
    precedence when both exist.

 -- Rick-GO <rickgijsberts@gocontroll.com>  Wed, 13 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200

go-identify (2.2.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Read modules from /lib/firmware/gocontroll/modules.json (new format) when the
    legacy colon-separated /lib/firmware/gocontroll/modules file is absent;
    legacy file takes precedence when both exist (backward compatibility).
  * CAN INTERFACES: removed State column (only Interface + Bitrate now).
  * CONTROLLER: prefer /sys/firmware/devicetree/base/platform over /hardware
    when present; fall back to /hardware when /platform is absent.
  * INSTALLED MODULES / CAN INTERFACES / INSTALLED GO-* TOOLS: append usage hint
    to title ("- go-modules for management", "- go-can for configurations",
    "- apt-get update - install") with the relevant commands in orange.
  * Fix: send a Debian APT-HTTP/1.3 User-Agent when fetching the apt.gocontroll.com
    manifest; Cloudflare blocks Python's default User-Agent with 403, which
    silently disabled the manifest column.
  * INSTALLED GO-* TOOLS: rename "Package" header to "go-*"; rename "Available"
    to "Manifest" and always show the apt manifest version (not only when
    newer); colour package names green when up-to-date, orange when an update
    is available on apt.gocontroll.com.
  * Box renderers are now ANSI-aware (visible-length aware padding/width
    calculations) so coloured titles and cells align correctly.
  * 4G MODEM: detect whether the go-wwan systemd service is active and, when
    inactive, surface a "Service" row with an enable hint
    (systemctl enable --now go-wwan, highlighted in orange). Detection is
    passive — the service is never started or stopped by identify itself.
  * _kv_box renderer is now ANSI-aware for cell values too, so coloured rows
    align correctly.
  * INSTALLED MODULES: auto-bootstrap by running `go-modules scan` when neither
    /lib/firmware/gocontroll/modules nor /lib/firmware/gocontroll/modules.json
    exists yet (a one-shot scan that writes the cache file). Explicit -s flag
    behaviour is unchanged.

 -- Rick-GO <rickgijsberts@gocontroll.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200

